%title sediments


= sediments=

===shore processes===
budgeting(source/sink)
- Gains:
    # longshore transport(ex.60,000m^3/yr)
    # cliff erosion(5000)
    # onshore transport(5000)
- Losses
    # wind(1000)
    # longshore transport(54000)
    # offhsore transport(20000)
===Deep sea sediments===
~200 Mil year
0.1-100's of cm/1000 year
- What how when why
- context
    - Tectonic setting (active, passive, Mid Ocean Ridge,)
    - Proximity to continent(river suuply glaciers)
    - Rate of supply(production of shells, erosion due to uplift, dam bursts)
    - chemical precipitation, dissolution(Hydro Thermal Vents, CO2 dissolution, oppo)
    - Different Classes(by the dominant *SOURCE*)
        - Terrigenous
        - Biogenous(Corals)!CaCO3 !SiO2
        - hydrogenous
        - Cosmogenous
- erosion
- deposition
- *SIZE* matters
    - boulder
    - cobble
    - pebble
    - granite
    - sand <2mm
    - silt <.062mm
    - clay

Coastal Cell::the area between the shore and the coastal islands.


